1 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES - FLOOR VERSION
2 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
3 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
4 HOUSE BILL 2951 By: Hardin of the House
5 and
6 Woods of the Senate
7
8
9 AS INTRODUCED
10 An Act relating to prisons and reformatories;
amending 57 O.S. 2021, Section 95, which relates to
11 the delivery of sentenced persons; authorizing the
transport of inmates to certain facility; amending 57
12 O.S. 2021, Sections 502, as amended by Section 2,
Chapter 22, O.S.L. 2023, 508, and 509, as last
13 amended by Section 2, Chapter 467, O.S.L. 2025 (57
O.S. Supp. 2025, Sections 502 and 509), which relate
14 to the Oklahoma Corrections Act of 1967; removing and
adding correctional centers to certain defined term;
15 updating reference to certain named act; deleting
certain salary restriction; adding correctional
16 centers to list of penal institutions maintained by
the Department of Corrections; repealing 57 O.S.
17 2021, Section 504.7, which relates to the Kate
Barnard Community Corrections Center; and providing
18 an effective date.
19
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
22 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 57 O.S. 2021, Section 95, is
23 amended to read as follows:
24
HB2951 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 Section 95. A. Any person convicted of an offense against the
2 laws of this state and sentenced to imprisonment that is not to be
3 served in a county jail shall be transported by the sheriff of the
4 county where the person is sentenced, or transported by a designated
5 representative of the sheriff, to the Department of Corrections at
6 the Lexington Assessment and Reception Center, the Mabel Bassett
7 Correctional Center, or other location designated by the Director of
8 the Department of Corrections.
9 B. Any person convicted of an offense against the laws of this
10 state and sentenced to imprisonment that is not to be served in a
11 county jail and who is not housed in a county jail shall be
12 transported by the detention center, or transported by a designated
13 representative of the detention center, to the Department of
14 Corrections at the Lexington Assessment and Reception Center, the
15 Mabel Bassett Correctional Center, or other location designated by
16 the Director of the Department of Corrections.
17 C. The sheriff shall deliver the person to the Department at
18 such center together with:
19 1. A certified copy of the judgment and sentence from the court
20 ordering such imprisonment, unless the judgment and sentence
21 previously has been sent electronically by an authorized clerk of
22 the court;
23
24
HB2951 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 2. A certificate setting forth the number of days served in the
2 county jail after the pronouncement of judgment and rendering of
3 sentence for the offenses committed;
4 3. A copy of any medical, dental, or mental health records of
5 the defendant for conditions reviewed or treated while in the
6 custody of the sheriff;
7 4. Any medication or medical or dental device prescribed for
8 the defendant while in the custody of the sheriff or for a
9 preexisting condition; and
10 5. A copy of the presentence investigation report, if a report
11 was prepared.
12 D. The Department of Corrections shall give the sheriff a
13 receipt for each person received into the custody of the Department.
14 The receipt shall be filed by the sheriff in the office of the clerk
15 of the court where the sentence was made.
16 E. The Department of Corrections shall reimburse the
17 transporting agency as follows:
18 1. Mileage from the county sheriff's office to the appropriate
19 reception center and back to the county sheriff's office; and
20 2. Hourly wage reimbursement for the transporting officer for
21 the hours of transport travel and time spent at the reception center
22 based on the transporting officer's normal hourly wage.
23 Reimbursement shall not exceed Thirty Dollars ($30.00) an hour per
24
HB2951 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 offi cer. Documentation of the officer's hourly wage shall accompany
2 all reimbursement requests to the Department.
3 The Department of Corrections shall have the authority to
4 promulgate rules and forms for the reimbursement procedures provided
5 in this section.
6 The Department of Corrections shall submit a quarterly report to
7 the Chair of the Senate Appropriations Committee and Chair of the
8 House of Representatives Appropriations and Budget Committee.
9 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 57 O.S. 2021, Section 502, as
10 amended by Section 2, Chapter 22, O.S.L. 2023 (57 O.S. Supp. 2025,
11 Section 502), is amended to read as follows:
12 Section 502. As used in this title, unless the context
13 otherwise requires:
14 1. "Board" means the State Board of Corrections;
15 2. "Department" means the Department of Corrections of this
16 state;
17 3. "Director" means the Director of the Department of
18 Corrections;
19 4. "Halfway house" means a private facility for the placement
20 of inmates in a community setting for the purpose of reintegrating
21 into the community inmates who are nearing their release dates. The
22 term shall not include private prisons;
23 5. "Institutions" means the Oklahoma State Penitentiary located
24 at McAlester, Oklahoma; the Oklahoma State Reformatory located at
